org.osmdroid.bonuspack.location
Class OverpassAPIProvider

java.lang.Object
  org.osmdroid.bonuspack.location.OverpassAPIProvider

public class OverpassAPIProvider
extends java.lang.Object

Access to Overpass API, a super-powerful search API on OpenStreetMap data.
Two strategies are implemented:
- Get result as POIs, as simplified content and geometry (one point), using getPOIsFromUrl(String)
- Get results with full content and geometry as KML, using addInKmlFolder(KmlFolder, String)
Helper methods are provided to build URLs for usual search requests.
TODO Improve/revise the API => add an API targeting boundaries?

urlForPOISearch

public java.lang.String urlForPOISearch(java.lang.String tag,
                                        org.osmdroid.util.BoundingBoxE6 bb,
                                        int limit,
                                        int timeout)
Build the URL to search for elements having a specific OSM Tag (key=value), within a bounding box. Elements will be OSM nodes, ways and relations. Ways and relations will have no geometry, only their center.
Usage: urlForPOISearch("amenity=cinema", map.getBoundingBox(), 200, 30);

Parameters:
tag - OpenStreetMap tag to search. Can be either "key=value", or "key".
bb - bounding box
limit - max number of results.
timeout - in seconds
Returns:
the url for this request.
See Also:
OSM Tags

getPOIsFromUrl

public java.util.ArrayList<POI> getPOIsFromUrl(java.lang.String url)
Search for POI.

Parameters:
url - full URL request, built with #urlForPOISearch or equivalent. Main requirements:
- Content must be in JSON format
- ways and relations must contain the "center" element.
Returns:
elements as a list of POI

urlForTagSearchKml

public java.lang.String urlForTagSearchKml(java.lang.String tag,
                                           org.osmdroid.util.BoundingBoxE6 bb,
                                           int limit,
                                           int timeout)
Build the URL to search for elements having a specific OSM Tag (key=value), within a bounding box. Similar to urlForPOISearch(java.lang.String, org.osmdroid.util.BoundingBoxE6, int, int), but here the request is built to retrieve the full geometry.

Parameters:
tag -
bb - bounding box
limit - max number of results.
timeout - in seconds
Returns:
the url for this request.

addInKmlFolder

public boolean addInKmlFolder(KmlFolder kmlFolder,
                              java.lang.String url)
Retrieve elements from url, and add them in a KML Folder, as KML Placemarks: Point, LineString, Polygon, or MultiGeometry.

Parameters:
kmlFolder - KML folder in which elements will be added
url - OverPass API url to retrieve elements. Main requirements:
- Content must be in JSON format
- ways and relations must have the "geometry" element
Returns:
true if ok, false if technical error.
